/*---------------------------------------------------------------------------*\
  vlle01_waterButanol  --  liquid-liquid flash of water + 1-butanol with the
  cited Winkelman et al. (2009) UNIQUAC LLE parameters.

  Water + 1-butanol is THE textbook partially-miscible binary.  At 320 K and
  1.013 bar an equimolar mixture is well below the bubble point (water boils at
  373 K, 1-butanol near 390 K), so the equilibrium is GENUINELY two LIQUIDS --
  no vapour.  A simple `phaseSet LL` flash (Michelsen TPD pre-check, then direct
  Gibbs-energy minimisation, multi-start Nelder-Mead) finds the split.

  THE PARAMETERS (cited, NOT fabricated -- see constant/propertyDict and
  README.md):  the UNIQUAC interaction parameters are the LLE-specific fit of

      J.G.M. Winkelman, G.N. Kraai, H.J. Heeres, Fluid Phase Equilibria 284
      (2009) 71-79, Table 2 (p.73); structural r,q from their Table 1 (p.72).

  with the full temperature dependence A_ij(T) = a_ij + b_ij*T + c_ij*T^2
  (their Eq. 10), tau_ij = exp(-A_ij/T) (their Eq. 7), valid 273-363 K.  The
  same numbers, fully provenanced, also live in
  data/standards/binaryPairs/UNIQUAC/nButanol-water.dat.

  WHAT THIS DEMONSTRATES:

      * a REAL liquid-liquid miscibility gap, reproduced from a cited primary
        source -- the water-rich phase is ~98.3 mol% water (~1.7 mol% butanol)
        and the butanol-rich phase is ~54 mol% water (~46 mol% butanol),
        matching Winkelman's Figs 1-2;
      * the IsothermalFlash LL branch: a Michelsen TPD stability test that flags
        the feed as unstable, then a direct Gibbs-minimisation that resolves the
        two coexisting compositions;
      * honest phase labelling -- the two output streams are named by their
        actual composition (waterRich / butanolRich), with alphaRich/betaRich
        hints steering which liquid lands in which slot.

  HISTORICAL NOTE: an earlier version of this case carried only a DECHEMA
  VLE-fit NRTL set, which (being a VLE fit) has NO miscibility gap, so the flash
  found a single liquid -- it was kept as an honest "VLE-fit-misses-LLE" lesson
  pending a cited LLE set.  Winkelman et al. (2009) IS that cited set, so the
  case now shows the genuine split.  (The VLE-blind NRTL lesson lives on in the
  NRTL catalogue file's provenance.)
\*---------------------------------------------------------------------------*/

// stream state lives on disk in 0/ (per-stream files); flowsheetDict is TOPOLOGY only

units
(
    {
        name        decanter01;
        type        isothermalFlash;
        in          feed;
        outputs     ( waterRich  butanolRich );

        operation
        {
            T          320.0 K;
            P          1.013 bar;
            phaseSet   LL;
            alphaRich  water;       // -> waterRich slot (alpha, ~98 mol% water)
            betaRich   nButanol;    // -> butanolRich slot (beta, ~46 mol% butanol)
        }

        compositionTol   1e-5;
        maxOuterIter     200;
    }
);
